text:
At 11:01 a.m. London time this morning, Kate Middleton gave birth to her third child, a baby boy. Royal press was stationed outside Lindo Wing, where Middleton and Prince William are due to come out with their new baby to introduce him to the press.

This content is imported from twitter. You may be able to find the same content in another format, or you may be able to find more information, at their web site. The world’s media are gathered outside the Lindo Wing at St Mary’s Hospital ahead of the birth of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge’s third child. pic.twitter.com/FLr1lL2AyT — The Prince and Princess of Wales (@KensingtonRoyal) April 23, 2018

But Lindo Wing, the maternity wing for all of St Mary’s Hospital hospital, was serving other couples too, including this man and woman who walked out the door with their new baby.

This content is imported from twitter. You may be able to find the same content in another format, or you may be able to find more information, at their web site. Unsuspecting couple have new baby - and find the world’s press waiting outside. pic.twitter.com/fWcBBefLDX — James Longman (@JamesAALongman) April 23, 2018

They were greeted by the press too, and Twitter had a field day reacting to the photos shared of the surprise encounter. It went so viral, it became a Twitter moment—and a future great story for the kid and his or her parents to tell all their friends.
